{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context / Problem\n\nWith the port defined (S2 [rebar:ce4d-c3ca-5412-4798]) and selection wired (S3\n[rebar:94f9-a9a0-7475-4e75]), the backend-neutral core still named Jira concretely â€” both by\nconstructing the Jira transport inline AND by importing the vendor field mappers directly. This\nstory routes the **transport-construction** sites through the `Backend` port so the core stops\nbuilding an `AcliClient` inline, and de-hardcodes the provider-identity `\"jira\"` literals.\n\n## Scope split (recorded at implementation time)\n\nThe original story bundled TWO kinds of rewiring. They were split because the second requires a\ndependency-injection refactor that fights the standalone `spec_from_file_location` test-loader\nconvention and is independently reviewable:\n\n- **Landed here (this change):** the four transport/construction sites, the provider-identity\n  literals, and the `apply_handlers` exception-class import â€” a behaviour-preserving change proven\n  by the full reconcile suite staying green.\n- **Split to follow-up [rebar:4af8-2d88-719e-4478]:** routing the core *importer* sites\n  (`outbound_differ`/`inbound_differ`/`apply_inbound`/`outbound_comments`/`inbound_translate`) off\n  the vendor mappers via injection, and single-sourcing the leak-fix constants\n  (`outbound_links._RELATION_TO_JIRA_LINK`, ADF-sizing, value-maps) under `adapters/jira/`.\n\n## Scope (landed)\n\nTransport/construction sites routed through `select_backend(load_config()).transport`:\n- `applier._load_acli` and `fetcher._load_acli` now return the backend transport directly.\n- `run_differs.py`'s outbound-diff client and `_attestation.build_acli_client_from_env()`\n  obtain the transport from the selected backend (fail-fast env behaviour preserved).\n- The jira factory builds the `AcliClient` with `resolve_jira_settings(project_default=\"DIG\")`\n  so the transport carries the project for every consumer.\n- `apply_handlers.py` catches `AssigneeNotFoundError` via a direct import (not `ctx.acli.â€¦`).\n- `apply_inbound_records.py`'s two provider-identity `\"jira\"` literals flow from the selected\n  backend's `vendor` (the `validate_creation_channel(\"jira\")` vocabulary key is retained).\n- ~34 `_load_acli` test doubles migrated module-shaped â†’ transport-shaped (assertions unchanged).\n\n## Testing\n\n- **Integration:** the full reconcile unit+integration suite stays green (behaviour-preserving).\n- **Neutrality gate:** a new test asserts no direct `AcliClient(` construction remains in the four\n  transport modules and `apply_inbound_records` carries exactly one `\"jira\"` token.\n- **Teeth:** perturbing the outbound delegation makes the characterization tests RED.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [x] `apply_inbound_records.py`'s two provider-identity `\"jira\"` literals (`:70,74`) are replaced\n  by the selected backend's `vendor`; `grep -n '\"jira\"' apply_inbound_records.py` returns exactly\n  one line (the retained `validate_creation_channel(\"jira\")` vocabulary key).\n- [x] The `applier`/`fetcher` `_load_acli` seams return the backend transport directly, across all\n  injection styles and the integration `_fakes.py` double; no seam double remains module-shaped â€”\n  verified by `make test` green.\n- [x] `run_differs.py` routes its outbound-diff client through `select_backend(config).transport`;\n  `grep -rn 'AcliClient(' run_differs.py` returns zero hits; covered by a new test.\n- [x] `_attestation.build_acli_client_from_env()` returns the selected backend's transport,\n  preserving fail-fast missing-env behaviour; `grep 'AcliClient(' _attestation.py` returns zero.\n- [x] `apply_handlers.py` catches `AssigneeNotFoundError` via a direct import (no `ctx.acli.â€¦`);\n  the assignee soft-fail path still works.\n- [x] The full reconcile suite yields identical outcomes to pre-story `main`;\n  `make lint && make typecheck && make test` all green; the neutrality gate is green.\n- [SPLIT â†’ rebar:4af8-2d88-719e-4478] Core importer sites stop importing the vendor mappers\n  (differ/apply modules) â€” deferred; needs the DI refactor.\n- [SPLIT â†’ rebar:4af8-2d88-719e-4478] ADF-sizing, value-maps, and the `outbound_links` link\n  constant single-sourced under `adapters/jira/` â€” deferred."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784761074908662001,"uuid":"58d4488c-1e8e-4d2f-bd60-dba7016ac326"}